<DOC><DOCNO> AP890731-0027 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-31-89 0411EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-BarricadedGunman     07-31 0172</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Barricaded Gunman,0178</SECOND><HEAD>Barricaded Gunman Shoots Up Detroit Police Car</HEAD><DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A gunman was barricaded in his house today aftershooting up a police car and firing on a passing helicopter inresponse to an effort by authorities to arrest him on an attemptedmurder charge.   ``He's shooting periodically and randomly,'' said policespokesman Sgt. George Anthony. ``He's well armed. The situation isextremely dangerous.''   The incident began in northeast Detroit about 9:45 p.m. Sunday,when the gunman opened fire on police from the neighboring city ofHighland Park who had arrived at his house to serve the warrant,Anthony said.   The gunman, whose name was not being disclosed, later fired manyrounds into a Detroit police car that responded to the shooting.There were no injuries, Anthony said.   Police sealed off the area and evacuated several dozenneighborhood residents.   The gunman also took shots at a police helicopter hovering overhis home, officials said.   Police could not immediately provide details on the warrant thatset off the episode.</TEXT></DOC>